You can't use `readFile` from a browser as it uses the `fs` module.

Use the [`load`](https://github.com/exceljs/exceljs/blob/master/lib/xlsx/xlsx.js#L257) function. I didn't see it documented in the README though...

```javascript
const resp = await fetch('report-template.xlsx');
const buf = await resp.arrayBuffer();
const wb = new Excel.Workbook();
const workbook = wb.xlsx.load(buf);
console.log(workbook);
```
